1) <strong>Cannot add COMPLETE .torrent release into Neoloader</strong>:<br />How to add a .torrent file into NeoLoader? When I add a .torrent file into Shareaza, the program search for a filename/foldername (multiple file torrent) in the library, if file exists, it hashes it and if the hash is identical to the hash in .torrent file it starts sharing it in BitTorrent network; otherwise Shareaza starts downloading. When I add a file to NeoLoader, the program always tries to download file, there's no way to stop download and point to already shared file.<br /><br />2) <strong>Older entries remain in the GUI</strong>:<br />Start and complete a BT download, click "Sub Files", then remove the entire download and click any "normal" (single) file in Shared category: you will see inactive Sub Files tab with the list of removed files from multi-file torrent.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3790">Zebra</a> — Sun Nov 09, 2014 5:32 pm</p><hr />
