Hoster upload as single file:<br /><br />after a file is succesfully uploaded to hosters (shared - transfer tab) uploaded counter get back to 0 while the downloaded one shows the amount uploaded (file Dimension 96.13MB). <br />this happened with ALMOST all hosters i could upload to (i assume this means the transfer was successful but with a visual bug). <br />  <br />Upload to Hoster service   tempsend.com status: connected (waiting for browser)transfering/none  is not finishing after sending 96.13 MB,<br />as i could see, when i was at the pc, i uploaded more than 172 MB, i think the file stopped uploading after 200% file amount transferred (i wasnt at the pc anymore!), BUT<br />it shows now 96.13 MB as Downloaded amount like other hosters. i couldnt  see if it hapened with more hoster cause i went bed.<br /><br />hoster uptobox.com  leaves both dl and ul counter to 0 after we transfer al the 96.13 mb, and starts again after a while, same with filebin.ca - mirrorcreator.com - dl.free.fr.<br /><br />sendspace.com cannot complete transfer the whole file, it stops before reaching  96.13, it stopped approsimatively  at 35+ MB<br /><br /><br />NL to NL transmissions (ask for clips if neeeded):<br /><br />Torrent: once you find another NL source via torrent, there will be 0.00 upload speed but (10.xx kbs overhead) and the other neoloader will see the same but as download.<br />Once the upload starts overhead drops, but when transfer finish overhead bug starts again.this overhead can reach 35kbs.<br /><br />Ed2k (Horde): if while  NL1 is uploading to NL2, NL2 gives his upload slot to NL1, NL2 download from NL1 slowly decrease till stalling. long story short: there can't be a <span style="text-decoration: underline">simultaneous</span> mutual transfer.<br /><br />Neontities: there is the chance u have an unexpected overhead like torrents but this never raised over 7 kbs.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1009">esher</a> — Sun Nov 02, 2014 5:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
